          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Transparency For Wounded Warriors Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) to provide a member of the uniformed services whose claim for traumatic injury under Servicemembers' Group Life Insurance is denied, at the time of such denial, a legal analysis of the denial and the information the VA relied on in making such decision. </p> <p>The VA may not use any reasoning not articulated in such analysis or information not provided to justify a further denial on appeal.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2017-10-12T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
